.TH "qeth_bridgeport_query_ports" 9 "qeth_bridgeport_query_ports" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
qeth_bridgeport_query_ports \- query local bridgeport status.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" qeth_bridgeport_query_ports
.BI "(struct qeth_card *card "  ","
.BI "enum qeth_sbp_roles *role "  ","
.BI "enum qeth_sbp_states *state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "card" 12
qeth_card structure pointer.
.IP "role" 12
Role of the port: 0-none, 1-primary, 2-secondary.
.IP "state" 12
State of the port: 0-inactive, 1-standby, 2-active.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns negative errno-compatible error indication or 0 on success.

'role' and 'state' are not updated in case of hardware operation failure.
